'''Eleko Beach''' opened in 1989 as a serene and private beach in the [[Lekki Peninsula]], about 30 miles east of the [[Lagos Island]]. Away from the hustles and bustles of the metropolis, it usually has an atmosphere of peace and tranquility.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/01/beach-holidays-2015-best-beaches-lagos/|title=Beach holidays 2015: Best beaches in Lagos|date=January 9, 2015|publisher=The Vanguard|accessdate=May 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.punchng.com/feature/vista/lagos-beaches-gearing-up-for-fun-seekers/ |title=Lagos beaches gearing up for fun-seekers |publisher=The Punch |date=December 15, 2012 |accessdate=May 10, 2015 |author1=Bosede Olusila-Obada |author2=Ademola Olonilua |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518074953/http://www.punchng.com/feature/vista/lagos-beaches-gearing-up-for-fun-seekers/ |archivedate=May 18, 2015 |df= }}</ref>

