'''Khasnor Johan''' is a [[Malaysians|Malaysian]] author and historian.
==Early and personal life== Johan married Australian political scientist and author [[Harold Crouch]] in 1973.<ref name="Honouring Harold Crouch">{{cite web | url=http://epress.anu.edu.au/apps/bookworm/view/Soeharto%E2%80%99s+New+Order+and+its+Legacy%3A+Essays+in+honour+of+Harold+Crouch/5331/preface.xhtml | title=Preface: Honouring Harold Crouch | publisher=Australian National University | accessdate=6 December 2013 | author=Jamie Mackie, Edward Aspinall and Greg Fealy}}</ref>
==Education== Johan studied at the [[University of Malaya]] (in [[Kuala Lumpur]]).<ref name=Mohd /> Her master's thesis, ''The Malay College, Kuala Kangsar, 1905-1941: British Policy of Education for Employment in the Federated Malay States.'' was published in 1969.<ref name=Mohd>{{cite book|author=Maimunah Mohd. Tahir (Ungku.)|title=Modern Malay Literary Culture: A Historical Perspective|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hFcfCkVKVsYC&pg=PA76|year=1987|publisher=Institute of Southeast Asian|isbn=978-9971-988-52-4|pages=76–}}</ref> Like [[Harold Crouch|her husband]],<ref name="Honouring Harold Crouch" /> Johan attained her PhD at [[Monash University]] in [[Melbourne]]. Her thesis, published in 1974, was ''The Administrative Elite in the Federated Malay States: An Aspect of Malaysian Social History.''<ref>{{cite news | title=The NST diary, DKL edition | work=New Straits Times | publisher=Financial Times Ltd. (via HighBeam Research) | date=7 September 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Bruce Gale|title=Politics and Public Enterprise in Malaysia|year=1981|publisher=Eastern Universities Press|isbn=978-9971-71-152-8|page=40}}</ref>
==Career== From 1974 to 1992, Johan taught history at [[National University of Malaysia]]<!---Source said "Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia" which redirected to National University of Malaysia]].---> Crouch also taught at the university, his tenure from 1976 to 1990. In 1991 he began teaching at [[Australian National University]] in [[Canberra]].<ref name="Honouring Harold Crouch" /><ref name="PDGS">{{cite web | url=http://www.pdgs.org/experts/i-crouch.htm | title=Harold A. Crouch | publisher=Partnership for Democratic Governance and Security (PDGS) | accessdate=6 December 2013}}</ref> Johan retired from teaching in 1992 and moved to Canberra.{{citation needed|date=December 2013}} She was living in Canberra in 2002.<ref>{{cite book|author1=Fan Hong|author2=J.A. Mangan|title=Sport in Asian Society: Past and present|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ivKMctjHr58C&pg=PA122|date=30 September 2002|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-203-49742-5|page=122}}</ref>
==Published works== Johan published works between 1969 and 2005 in [[English language|English]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://orlabs.oclc.org/identities/lccn-n85-895 | title=Kasnor Johan | publisher=WorldCat | accessdate=6 December 2013}}</ref>
